olive oil
1 parsnip
1 sachet dried oregano
½ pear
1 packet red pesto
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet chicken breast
½ tbs plain flour
drizzle red wine vinegar
1 bag salad leaves
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
2 Kumara

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Peel kumara. Cut kumara and
parsnip into bite-sized chunks.
• Place kumara, parsnip and dried oregano on a lined oven tray. Drizzle
generously with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Add
a dash of water to tray and roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• While veggies are roasting, thinly slice pear (see ingredients).
• In a small bowl, combine red pesto and mayonnaise. Set aside.
• Place your hand flat on top of each chicken breast and use a sharp knife to
slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a medium bowl, combine plain flour and Nan's special seasoning, then
season. Working in batches, dip chicken into flour mixture to coat, then
transfer to a plate.

• When veggies have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with enough olive oil to coat the base of pan.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken, in batches, until golden and cooked through,
3-4 minutes each side. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towel.
• Meanwhile, combine a drizzle of red wine vinegar and olive oil in a large
bowl, then season. Add pear and mixed salad leaves and toss to coat.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer pink inside.

• Slice seared chicken.
• Divide chicken, oregano-roasted veggies and pear salad between plates.
• Serve with red pesto mayo.